Jeff Wicks, News24The pig snout that was left on the gate of a mosque in Smon's Town, Cape Town. (Facebook) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - The Muslim Judicial Council [MJC] has condemned a case of Islamaphobia in Simon&rsquo;s Town after a pig's nose and blood was left on the door of a mosque on Saturday.News of the issue was spread on social media.Ghalib Jonker posted on Facebook: &ldquo;Some terrible news. This morning after Fajr a pig&rsquo;s nose and blood was left on the Simon&rsquo;s Town Mosque door&hellip;the police were called and they said that there is nothing they can do so they are not opening a case&rdquo;.He made a plea for those responsible to be brought to justice.The MJC&rsquo;s Moulana AK Allie confirmed that the attack had taken place.&ldquo;The MJC condemns violations of human dignity in all forms irrespective of religion and in this regard I can say that the matter is under investigation,&rdquo; he said. &nbsp;&ldquo;We condemn this violation and we stand up for all religions in our country. We have called on our community to deal with this in a discerning matter while abiding by the laws of the land. We want the authorities to bring whoever is responsible to book.&rdquo; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.